dies]]||8||4||3||1||17||9|| 8||'''15'''\n|-\n|4||align=\"left\"|[[Angeviolet Hiroshima]]||8||0||3||5||4||13|| -9||'''3'''\n|-\n|5||align=\"left\"|[[FC Kibi International University Charme]]||8||0||3||5||6||23|| -17||'''3'''\n|}\n\n====Final Round====\n=====Semifinals=====\n*[[Nojima Stella Kanagawa Sagamihara]] 1-1 (pen 3-5) [[AS Harima ALBION]]\n*[[Cerezo Osaka Sakai Ladies]] 2-3 [[Nippon Sport Science University Fields Yokohama]]\n\n=====Final=====\n*[[AS Harima ALBION]] 2-0 [[Nippon Sport Science University Fields Yokohama]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Nadeshiko League Cup}}\n{{2016 in Japanese football}}\n\n[[Category:Nadeshiko League Cup]]\n[[Category:2016 in Japanese women's football]]\n", "name_user": "Frietjes", "label": "safe", "comment": "expand templates perFb team TfD outcomeandFb competition TfD outcomeandFb cl TfD outcomeandFb rbr TfD outcome", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2016_Nadeshiko_League_Cup"}
{"title_page": "Siu yeh", "text_new": "{{Meals}}\n{{Chinese\n|pic=Street food in Causeway Bay.JPG\n|piccap=A snack shop in [[Causeway Bay]], [[Hong Kong]] selling snacks for ''siu yeh''\n|t=[[wikt:\u5bb5|\u5bb5]][[wikt:\u591c|\u591c]]|s=[[wikt:\u5bb5|\u5bb5]][[wikt:\u591c|\u591c]]\n|j=siu1 je2\n|y=s\u012bu y\u00e9\n|p=xi\u0101o y\u00e8\n|l=\u5bb5 - overnight<br>\u591c - night}}\n\n'''Siu yeh''' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: [[wikt:\u5bb5|\u5bb5]][[wikt:\u591c|\u591c]] / \u6d88\u591c; [[pinyin]]: Xi\u0101oy\u00e8), also known as '''yexiao''' (\u591c\u5bb5; [[pinyin]]: y\u00e8xi\u0101o), is a late night [[meal]] in the [[Cuisine of Hong Kong|food culture of Hong Kong]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/siu-yeh-hong-kong-food-culture-late-night-restaurants|title=Hong Kong Takes Its Late-Night Snacks Seriously|last=Liao|first=Christina|website=Vogue|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>, [[Taiwanese cuisine|Taiwan]], and some parts of [[northern and southern China|southern mainland China]]. It comes after [[dinner]], and is similar to [[supper]]. Mealtime may start from about 9pm onwards until 4am, which would be early morning [[yum cha]] time. It can range anywhere from a snack to a full-fledged meal. For people working late night shifts, siu yeh is also associated with their post-midnight meals<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/travel/story/20160829-hong-kongs-secret-night-meal|title=Hong Kong's secret night meal|last=Treleaven|first=Sarah|website=www.bbc.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>. \n\n\n\n==See also==\n*[[Supper]]\n*[[Hong Kong cuisine]]\n*[[Daa Laang]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Siu Yeh}}\n[[Category:Hong Kong cuisine]]\n\n\n{{HongKong-stub}}\n{{food-stub}}\n{{Hong Kong cuisine}}\n", "text_old": "{{Meals}}\n{{Chinese|pic=Street food in Causeway Bay.JPG|piccap=A snack shop in [[Causeway Bay]], [[Hong Kong]] selling snacks for ''siu yeh''|t=[[wikt:\u5bb5|\u5bb5]][[wikt:\u591c|\u591c]]|s=[[wikt:\u5bb5|\u5bb5]][[wikt:\u591c|\u591c]]|j=siu1 je2|y=s\u012bu y\u00e9|p=xi\u0101o y\u00e8|l=\u5bb5 - overnight<br>\u591c - night}}\n\n'''Siu yeh''' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: [[wikt:\u5bb5|\u5bb5]][[wikt:\u591c|\u591c]] / \u6d88\u591c; [[pinyin]]: Xi\u0101oy\u00e8), also known as '''yexiao''' (\u591c\u5bb5; [[pinyin]]: y\u00e8xi\u0101o), is a late night [[meal]] in the [[Cuisine of Hong Kong|food culture of Hong Kong]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/siu-yeh-hong-kong-food-culture-late-night-restaurants|title=Hong Kong Takes Its Late-Night Snacks Seriously|last=Liao|first=Christina|website=Vogue|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>, [[Taiwanese cuisine|Taiwan]], and some parts of [[northern and southern China|southern mainland China]]. It comes after [[dinner]], and is similar to [[supper]]. Mealtime may start from about 9pm onwards until 4am, which would be early morning [[yum cha]] time. It can range anywhere from a snack to a full-fledged meal. For people working late night shifts, siu yeh is also associated with their post-midnight meals<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/travel/story/20160829-hong-kongs-secret-night-meal|title=Hong Kong's secret night meal|last=Treleaven|first=Sarah|website=www.bbc.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>. \n\n\n\n==See also==\n*[[Supper]]\n*[[Hong Kong cuisine]]\n*[[Daa Laang]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Siu Yeh}}\n[[Category:Hong Kong cuisine]]\n\n\n{{HongKong-stub}}\n{{food-stub}}\n{{Hong Kong cuisine}}\n", "name_user": "17jiangz1", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siu_yeh"}
{"title_page": "AVR (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 film by Arindam Sharma}}\n{{EngvarB|date = April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = AVR\n| image          = Poster_Of_AVR_Assamese_Film.jpg\n| director       = [[Arindam Sharma]]\n| producer       = Brojendra Nath Sarma\n| writer         = Arindam Sharma\n| starring       = {{unbulleted list|[[Arnab Ayan]]|[[Ajay Barman]]|Niha Rani Das|Bikash Borah|}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Kailash Duarah\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2020|10|23|}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Assamese\n| studio         = Krishna Kraft Productions \n}}\n'''''AVR : Advik Vs. Ray''''' is an upcoming 2020 Indian [[Assamese cinema|Assamese-language]] [[Super Hero|science fiction]] [[action film]] written and directed by [[Arindam Sharma]] and starring [[Arnab Ayan]] and Niha Rani Das in the lead roles and [[Ajay Barman]] in lead villain. The film is produced by Brojendra Nath Sarma under Krishna Kraft Productions.\n\nThe film\u2019s cinematography is done by Kailash Duarah. Its a film having 600 VFX shots. AVR is scheduled to be released on 23rd October 2020.<ref>1.{{Cite web|url=https://rupaliparda.com/archives/12430|title=\u0986\u09b9\u09bf \u0986\u099b\u09c7 \"AVR: Advik Vs Ray\"- \u098f\u0996\u09a8 \u0985\u09b8\u09ae\u09c0\u09af\u09bc\u09be \"\u099a\u09c1\u09aa\u09be\u09f0\u09b9\u09bf\u09f0\u09cb\" \u099b\u09ac\u09bf\u0983|website=rupaliparda.com}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* Arnab Ayan as Advik, Pranay\n* [[Ajay Barman]] as Ray, Dr.Roy\n* Niha Rani Das as Sneha (Pranay's Wife)\n* Bikash Borah as Pratik (Pranay's Brother)\n* Nilutpal Borah as Nill (Pranay's Friend)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n2.{{Cite web|url=https://assamtimespost.com/?p=17846|title=\u0986\u09b9\u09bf \u0986\u099b\u09c7 \u0985\u09b8\u09ae\u09c0\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09a4 \u098f\u0996\u09a8 \"\u099a\u09c1\u09aa\u09be\u09f0\u09b9\u09bf\u09f0\u09cb' \u099a\u09bf\u09a8\u09c7\u09ae\u09be\"\u0964 \u09a8\u09f1\u09be\u0997\u09a4 \u09aa\u09f0\u09bf\u099a\u09be\u09b2\u0995 \u0985\u09f0\u09bf\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\u09ae \u09b6\u09f0\u09cd\u09ae\u09be\u09f0 \u09aa\u09f0\u09bf\u099a\u09be\u09b2\u09a8\u09be\u09f0\u09c7 \u09a8\u09bf\u09f0\u09cd\u09ae\u09bf\u09a4 \u098f\u0987 \u099b\u09ac\u09bf\u0996\u09a8\u09f0 \u09a8\u09be\u09ae \u09b9\u09c8\u099b\u09c7 \"AVR: Advik Vs Ray\"|last=|first=|date=31 March 2020|website=ASSAM TIMES POST|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}\n\n== External Links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt11912238|AVR:Advik Vs Ray}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:Assamese-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=AVR (2020 film)|timestamp=20200415152424|year=2020|month=April|day=15|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=AVR (2020 film)|date=15 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{short description|2020 film by Arindam Sharma}}\n{{EngvarB|date = April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = AVR\n| image          = Poster_Of_AVR_Assamese_Film.jpg\n| director       = [[Arindam Sharma]]\n| producer       = Brojendra Nath Sarma\n| writer         = Arindam Sharma\n| starring       = {{unbulleted list|[[Arnab Ayan]]|[[Ajay Barman]]|Niha Rani Das|Bikash Borah|}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Kailash Duarah\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2020|10|23|}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Assamese\n| studio         = Krishna Kraft Productions \n}}\n'''''AVR : Advik Vs. Ray''''' is an upcoming 2020 Indian [[Assamese cinema|Assamese-language]] [[Super Hero|science fiction]] [[action film]] written and directed by [[Arindam Sharma]] and starring [[Arnab Ayan]] and Niha Rani Das in the lead roles and [[Ajay Barman]] in lead villain. The film is produced by Brojendra Nath Sarma under Krishna Kraft Productions.\n\nThe film\u2019s cinematography is done by Kailash Duarah. Its a film having 600 VFX shots. AVR is scheduled to be released on 23rd October 2020.<ref>1.{{Cite web|url=https://rupaliparda.com/archives/12430|title=\u0986\u09b9\u09bf \u0986\u099b\u09c7 \"AVR: Advik Vs Ray\"- \u098f\u0996\u09a8 \u0985\u09b8\u09ae\u09c0\u09af\u09bc\u09be \"\u099a\u09c1\u09aa\u09be\u09f0\u09b9\u09bf\u09f0\u09cb\" \u099b\u09ac\u09bf\u0983|website=rupaliparda.com}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* Arnab Ayan as Advik, Pranay\n* [[Ajay Barman]] as Ray, Dr.Roy\n* Niha Rani Das as Sneha (Pranay's Wife)\n* Bikash Borah as Pratik (Pranay's Brother)\n* Nilutpal Borah as Nill (Pranay's Friend)\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n2.{{Cite web|url=https://assamtimespost.com/?p=17846|title=\u0986\u09b9\u09bf \u0986\u099b\u09c7 \u0985\u09b8\u09ae\u09c0\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09a4 \u098f\u0996\u09a8 \"\u099a\u09c1\u09aa\u09be\u09f0\u09b9\u09bf\u09f0\u09cb' \u099a\u09bf\u09a8\u09c7\u09ae\u09be\"\u0964 \u09a8\u09f1\u09be\u0997\u09a4 \u09aa\u09f0\u09bf\u099a\u09be\u09b2\u0995 \u0985\u09f0\u09bf\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\u09ae \u09b6\u09f0\u09cd\u09ae\u09be\u09f0 \u09aa\u09f0\u09bf\u099a\u09be\u09b2\u09a8\u09be\u09f0\u09c7 \u09a8\u09bf\u09f0\u09cd\u09ae\u09bf\u09a4 \u098f\u0987 \u099b\u09ac\u09bf\u0996\u09a8\u09f0 \u09a8\u09be\u09ae \u09b9\u09c8\u099b\u09c7 \"AVR: Advik Vs Ray\"|last=|first=|date=31 March 2020|website=ASSAM TIMES POST|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}\n\n== External Links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt11912238|AVR:Advik Vs Ray}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:Assamese-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n", "name_user": "AssameseReporter", "label": "safe", "comment": "This article is true please so that I deleted deletion nomination option", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AVR_(2020_film)"}
{"title_page": "Poh Li San", "text_new": "{{Infobox candidate\n| name        = Poh Li San\n| birth_date  = 19 November 1975\n| birth_place = [[Singapore]]\n| residence   = Singapore\n| education   = Bachelor of Science (Engineering), Bachelor of Arts (Economics)\n| alma_mater  = [[Dunman High School]], [[Temasek Junior College]], [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]]\n| occupation  = Vice-President at [[Changi Airport Group]]\n| image       = Poh_Li_San,_Headshot.jpg\n}}\n\nPoh Li San ([[Simplified Chinese characters|simplified Chinese]]: \u5085\u4e3d\u73ca; born 19 November 1975), is the Vice-President of [[Changi Airport Group]] (CAG)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.changiairport.com/content/dam/cacorp/publications/Changi%20Connections/2013/CAG-issue21_final_view.pdf|title=Changi Connection Issue 21|last=|first=|date=September 2013|website=Changi Airport|publisher=Changi Airport Group|pages=4|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714132131/https://www.changiairport.com/content/dam/cacorp/publications/Changi%20Connections/2013/CAG-issue21_final_view.pdf|archive-date=July 2019|access-date=}}</ref>. Poh is a recipient of the [[Singapore Armed Forces]] (SAF) [https://www.mindef.gov.sg/oms/scholarship/scholarships-smsw.html Merit (Women) Overseas] [[Scholarship]] <ref name=\":0\" />, and the first female full-time [[Aide-de-camp|Aide-de-Camp]] to then President of the [[Singapore|Republic Of Singapore]], the late [[S. R. Nathan]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://singaporerecords.com/government-and-society/|title=Government And Society {{!}} Singapore Book Of Records|last=|first=|date=|website=Singaporerecords.com|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>. A member of the country's governing [[People's Action Party]] (PAP), she currently serves as the Deputy Chairman of the Sembawang Branch in Sembawang GRC<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/too-soon-to-tell-if-i-will-be-a-pap-candidate-says-changi-vp-poh-li-san|title=I'm willing to enter politics if offered the chance, says Changi Airport Group vice-president Poh Li San|last=|first=|date=2019-03-24|website=The Straits Times|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>. \n\n== Education ==\nPoh was educated in [[Dunman High School]] and [[Temasek Junior College]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://core.com.sg/collaterals/imgs/saf.pdf|title=Life cannot be examined in a routine office job.|last=|first=|date=2001|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415114932/http://core.com.sg/collaterals/imgs/saf.pdf|archive-date=April 2020|access-date=}}</ref>. She graduated in 1998 from the [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign|University of Illinois at Urbana Champaign]] with a Bachelor of Science (Engineering) degree with highest honours; and a Bachelor of Arts (Economics) degree with [[Summa Cum Laude]] and the highest distinction in Economics<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/li-san-poh-9243741/|title=Poh Li San's Profile|last=|first=|date=|website=Poh's LinkedIn Profile|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>. She was awarded the Bronze Tablet for graduating in the top 3% in her cohort<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107154745/https://digital.library.illinois.edu/items/af9a5300-13c4-0134-1d5f-0050569601ca-8|title=1998 University Honors|last=|first=|date=1998|website=University of Illinois Library|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107154745/https://digital.library.illinois.edu/items/af9a5300-13c4-0134-1d5f-0050569601ca-8|archive-date=November 2019|access-date=}}</ref>.\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Military Career ===\nPoh was awarded the [[Singapore Armed Forces]] Merit (Women) Overseas [[Scholarship]] in 1994 <ref name=\":0\" /> and began her military career with the [[Republic of Singapore Air Force]] (RSAF) as a [[helicopter pilot]] after completing her studies<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://headtopics.com/sg/mainstream-media-speculates-that-saf-scholar-and-ex-pilot-could-be-fielded-as-pap-candidate-in-next-4667781|title=Mainstream media speculates that SAF scholar and ex-pilot could be fielded as PAP candidate in next GE|last=|first=|date=|website=Head Topics|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>. She flew the [[Super Puma]] helicopter in 125 Squadron, Sembawang Airbase. Poh was a [[Search and rescue|Search and Rescue]] pilot and was part of the [[Singapore Armed Forces|SAF]] Humanitarian and Relief mission to [[Aceh]] following the [[Boxing Day Tsunami]]<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/air-force-veteran-in-pilots-seat-of-t4-project|title=Air force veteran in pilot's seat of T4 project|last=|first=|date=2014-04-02|website=The Straits Times|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2003, Poh assumed the role of Assistant Director of the Future Systems Technology Directorate under the [[Ministry of Defence (Singapore)|Ministry of Defence]] (MINDEF) and led the development of the latest technologies and formulated long term force development strategies and new war-fighting concepts for the [[Singapore Armed Forces|SAF]]<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.471.8043&rep=rep1&type=pdf|title=Journal of the Singapore Armed Forces|last=|first=|date=2007|website=|pages=26|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mindef.gov.sg/web/portal/mindef/about-us/organisation/organisation-profile/future-systems-technology-directorate/!ut/p/z1/jZDNDoIwEISfiHSpIHJENIjhT0XFXkyjBZsAJVBM9OltjIkHI7q3Tb6Z3RlEUIZITa-8oJKLmpZqP5Dx0Ypn7gIMHMVmqoOzS9PAnEbYd0do_wTileHpBuAgDtemAmx7kkKCwbMQ-UcPX8aB__QDABm2X_46oBrAbeiGBSINlReN17lAWd7LvmVad-skqzpNstOlFqUobtqZt-wkRUslU8-RIXsPrBfw7m_nWQpI_PHS3ugwxx_AZ8G_IjbVdpvdg3zjc-cBWJUwoA!!/dz/d5/L2dBISEvZ0FBIS9nQSEh/|title=MINDEF Singapore|website=www.mindef.gov.sg|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>. In 2005, Poh was made Flight Commander of 125 Squadron, Sembawang Airbase<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":5\" />.\n\nIn July 2006, Poh was selected to be the first female [[aide-de-camp]] to then President of the [[Singapore|Republic of Singapore]], the late [[S. R. Nathan]]<ref name=\":1\" />. She was responsible for planning and organising state-level visits, meetings, ceremonies, and events.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn May 2010, Poh left the [[Republic of Singapore Air Force|RSAF]] as [[Major]]<ref name=\":5\" /> and joined [[Changi Airport Group]].\n\n=== Post-Military Career ===\nPoh started her career in [[Changi Airport Group]] as Head, Budget Terminal in May 2010. She was in charge of the operations of the [[Budget terminal|Changi Airport Budget Terminal]]<ref name=\":3\" />. From 2012 to 2017, Poh led the planning and development of the new Terminal 4 where many new innovations and technologies were implemented to improve passenger experience and productivity. She is currently the Vice-President of the Terminal 5 planning and is responsible for the planning of specialised airport engineering systems for the new terminal<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://asia.blog.terrapinn.com/aviation/2018/05/15/interview-changi-airports-vp-terminal-5-planning-offering-excellent-airport-experience/|title=Interview: Changi Airport\u2019s VP of Terminal 5 Planning on offering excellent airport experience|date=2018-05-15|website=Aviation Festival Asia|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>.\n\nPoh joined the governing [[People's Action Party]] (PAP) as an activist in 2018. She is an active [[grassroots]] leader in [[Sembawang Group Representation Constituency|Sembawang GRC]], where she helped [[Member of parliament|Member of Parliament]] (MP) and [[Minister for Education (Singapore)|Minister for Education]] [[Ong Ye Kung]] in his [[Meet-the-People Sessions]] every Monday in his Gambas Ward<ref name=\":2\" />. She is currently the Deputy Chairman of the [[People's Action Party|PAP]] Sembawang Branch of [[Sembawang Group Representation Constituency|Sembawang GRC]] and sits on the Citizen's Consultative Committee of the ward as Vice-Chairman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbtc.org.sg/uploads/files/Sayang_Sembawang_Dec_2019.pdf|title=Sayang Sembawang Dec 2019 Issue|last=|first=|date=December 2019|website=Sembawang Town Council|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>, under [[Member of parliament|MP]] and [[Co-ordinating Minister for Infrastructure]] and [[Minister for Transport (Singapore)|Minister for Transport]] [[Khaw Boon Wan]].<br />\n\n== Personal Life ==\nPoh\u2019s father was a school teacher and her mother was an accounts clerk. She was born as a [[Singaporeans|Singaporean]] of [[Hokkien]] descent and a [[Christians|Christian]] by faith. Poh is single. She enjoys [[running]] and has completed more than ten full [[Marathon|marathons]] locally and overseas<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.giving.sg/president-s-challenge/poh_li_san_running_to_champion_progress|title=Relay Majulah - Poh Li San Running To Champion Progress in The Lives of Our Community In Need by President's Challenge|website=Giving.sg|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://corporate.sph.com.sg/media_releases/628|title=Media Releases - Singapore Press Holdings|website=corporate.sph.com.sg|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mindef.gov.sg/oms/content/imindef/publications/pointer/monographs/mono3/_jcr_content/imindefPars/0005/file.res/VFOT.pdf|title=A Vision For Our Time|last=|first=|date=|website=MINDEF|pages=6|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox candidate\n| name                = Poh Li San\n| birth_date          = 19 November 1975\n| birth_place         = Singapore\n| citizenship         = [[Singaporean]]\n| residence           = [[Singapore]]\n| education           = Bachelor of Science (Engineering), Bachelor of Arts (Economics)\n| alma_mater          = [[Dunman High School]], [[Temasek Junior College]], [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign]]\n| occupation          = Vice-President at [[Changi Airport Group]]\n| image               = [[File:Poh_Li_San,_Headshot.jpg|thumb|center]]\n}}\n\nPoh Li San ([[Simplified Chinese characters|simplified Chinese]]: \u5085\u4e3d\u73ca; born 19 November 1975), is the Vice-President of [[Changi Airport Group]] (CAG)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.changiairport.com/content/dam/cacorp/publications/Changi%20Connections/2013/CAG-issue21_final_view.pdf|title=Changi Connection Issue 21|last=|first=|date=September 2013|website=Changi Airport|publisher=Changi Airport Group|pages=4|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714132131/https://www.changiairport.com/content/dam/cacorp/publications/Changi%20Connections/2013/CAG-issue21_final_view.pdf|archive-date=July 2019|access-date=}}</ref>. Poh is a recipient of the [[Singapore Armed Forces]] (SAF) [https://www.mindef.gov.sg/oms/scholarship/scholarships-smsw.html Merit (Women) Overseas] [[Scholarship]] <ref name=\":0\" />, and the first female full-time [[Aide-de-camp|Aide-de-Camp]] to then [[President]] of the [[Singapore|Republic Of Singapore]], the late [[S. R. Nathan]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://singaporerecords.com/government-and-society/|title=Government And Society {{!}} Singapore Book Of Records|last=|first=|date=|website=Singaporerecords.com|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>. A member of the country's governing [[People's Action Party]] (PAP), she currently serves as the Deputy Chairman of the Sembawang Branch in Sembawang GRC<ref name=\":2\">{{C